		"body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nThis PR fixes an issue on Android where the tag association modal sometimes leaves a blank gap at the bottom after the on-screen keyboard is opened and then dismissed. The issue occurs because the modal layout does not properly resize after the keyboard hides. The changes improve keyboard state tracking and adjust modal behavior to ensure the layout recalculates correctly.\r\n\r\n## Details\r\n\r\n- Added a dependency array to the `useKeyboardState` hook to stabilize keyboard event listeners.\r\n- Updated `KeyboardAvoidingView` behavior for Android devices (API ≥ 35) to use `height` instead of `padding`.\r\n- Adjusted scroll overflow handling in `NoteTagsDialog` to prevent layout issues after keyboard dismissal.\r\n- Ensured the modal container properly resizes when the keyboard visibility changes.\r\n- No changes were made to existing tag logic or modal functionality beyond keyboard handling.\r\n\r\n# Testing\r\n\r\n- Tested on Android Emulator (API 36).\r\n- Opened a note and launched the **Tag association dialog**.\r\n- Focused on the **Search tags** input to trigger the keyboard.\r\n- Dismissed the keyboard and verified the modal layout.\r\n- Confirmed that the blank gap no longer appears.\r\n\r\n### Related Issue\r\n\r\n- Fixes #14722\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n\r\n- No database, synchronization, or tag management logic was modified.\r\n- The fix only improves modal layout recalculation when the keyboard is dismissed.\r\n\r\nBefore: \r\n<img width=\"492\" height=\"960\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3a7a3b10-54dc-42c5-9456-363e1dcf38f2\" />\r\n\r\nAfter: \r\n<img width=\"478\" height=\"988\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4488327b-b877-4c5d-92cd-4599c3c72c7a\" />\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/43308300-e86f-4884-8a8a-b6ebae87d1d5\r\n\r\n",
