			"body": "<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: summarize by coderabbit.ai -->\nNo actionable comments were generated in the recent review. 🎉\n\n<details>\n<summary>ℹ️ Recent review info</summary>\n\n<details>\n<summary>⚙️ Run configuration</summary>\n\n**Configuration used**: Path: .coderabbit.yaml\n\n**Review profile**: CHILL\n\n**Plan**: Pro\n\n**Run ID**: `e2436aa3-d899-446e-9658-346fbcc3da2f`\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>📥 Commits</summary>\n\nReviewing files that changed from the base of the PR and between 71eb260d5b421c1f3710ffd07307228f0633f46b and a318c8be09615f1a8484245d7ea9c7ffc515a85c.\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>📒 Files selected for processing (1)</summary>\n\n* `packages/app-mobile/components/screens/NoteTagsDialog.tsx`\n\n</details>\n\n</details>\n\n---\n\n\n<!-- walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>📝 Walkthrough</summary>\n\n## Walkthrough\n\nPlatform-aware keyboard handling: KeyboardAvoidingView now selects 'height' for newer Android versions; NoteTagsDialog modal scrolling/overflow is conditional by platform and container gains flex styling; keyboard listeners in useKeyboardState are mounted once on component mount.\n\n## Changes\n\n|Cohort / File(s)|Summary|\n|---|---|\n|**Keyboard Behaviour Component** <br> `packages/app-mobile/components/KeyboardAvoidingView.tsx`|Import `Platform`; compute `behavior` as `Platform.OS === 'android' && Platform.Version >= 35 ? 'height' : 'padding'`; replace hardcoded `'padding'` and add explanatory comment.|\n|**Tag Dialog UI Component** <br> `packages/app-mobile/components/screens/NoteTagsDialog.tsx`|Import `Platform`; expand exported `Props` to include `noteId: string | null`, `onCloseRequested?: () => void`, and `tags: TagEntity[]`; make `modalPropOverrides.scrollOverflow` platform-conditional (`true` on iOS with `keyboardShouldPersistTaps: true`, `false` on Android); add `flex: 1` to container style.|\n|**Keyboard Hook** <br> `packages/app-mobile/utils/hooks/useKeyboardState.ts`|Add empty dependency array to `useEffect` so keyboard listeners register on mount and cleanup on unmount (effect no longer re-runs each render).|\n\n## Sequence Diagram(s)\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant User\n    participant NoteTagsDialog\n    participant KeyboardAvoidingView\n    participant OS_Keyboard\n\n    User->>NoteTagsDialog: open tag dialog & focus input\n    NoteTagsDialog->>OS_Keyboard: request keyboard\n    OS_Keyboard->>KeyboardAvoidingView: keyboardDidShow\n    KeyboardAvoidingView->>NoteTagsDialog: adjust layout (behavior computed by Platform)\n    NoteTagsDialog->>User: render adjusted modal (scrollOverflow conditional)\n    User->>OS_Keyboard: dismiss keyboard\n    OS_Keyboard->>KeyboardAvoidingView: keyboardDidHide\n    KeyboardAvoidingView->>NoteTagsDialog: restore layout\n```\n\n## Suggested reviewers\n\n- Kaushalendra-Marcus\n\n</details>\n\n<!-- walkthrough_end -->\n\n\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>🚥 Pre-merge checks | ✅ 6</summary>\n\n<details>\n<summary>✅ Passed checks (6 passed)</summary>\n\n|               Check name              | Status   | Explanation                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 |\n| :-----------------------------------: | :------- | :-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n|              Title check              | ✅ Passed | The title clearly and specifically describes the main fix: addressing keyboard dismissal gap in the tag association modal on Android, directly matching the primary objective of issue `#14722`.                                                                                                                              |\n|           Description check           | ✅ Passed | The description is well-detailed and directly related to the changeset, explaining the Android keyboard issue, the specific fixes applied, testing methodology, and including before/after evidence of the fix.                                                                                                             |\n|          Linked Issues check          | ✅ Passed | The changes directly address issue `#14722`'s requirements: adding dependency array to useKeyboardState stabilises keyboard listeners, KeyboardAvoidingView behaviour adjustment for Android API ≥35 improves layout handling, and NoteTagsDialog scroll overflow adjustment prevents layout issues after keyboard dismissal. |\n|       Out of Scope Changes check      | ✅ Passed | All changes are directly related to fixing the keyboard dismissal gap issue in the tag association modal; no out-of-scope modifications to unrelated functionality, database logic, or tag management were introduced.                                                                                                      |\n|           Docstring Coverage          | ✅ Passed | No functions found in the changed files to evaluate docstring coverage. Skipping docstring coverage check.                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |\n| Pr Description Must Follow Guidelines | ✅ Passed | The pull request description contains all three required sections: problem statement describing the keyboard-induced blank gap issue, solution explaining the four changes made, and test plan with verification details and before/after images.             